        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="features feature-collapse versioned-section">
    <div class="text">
      <h2>Version controlled</h2>
      <p>
        Because timesheets are stored with your code, easily diff work times across branches to
        quickly determine the time spent on individual features.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="glyph glyph-versioned">
      <div class="timecard-state one">Today</div>
      <div class="timecard-state two">Yesterday</div>
      <div class="timecard-state three">Last Week</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="features feature-collapse owndata-section">
    <div class="text">
      <h2>Own your data</h2>
      <p>
        When your data is in your hands, you can ensure what should stay private will.
        Should you ever want to migrate data to another service, it's easily accessible
        and versioned along with your code.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="glyph glyph-owndata">
      <img src="/img/paw.svg" />
      <i class="fa fa-lock"></i>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="features features-metrics">
  <a name="metrics"></a>
  <div class="text">
    <h1>Metrics that matter</h1>
    <p>
      Other than a simple way to manage time, Waltz also gives you insight into
      your work trends. When we give you data that easily summarizes the state of
      a project and its clients, you get a clearer view into who contributed, what
      has been completed, and when a task has been completed.
    </p>
  </div>
  
  <div class="right">
    <div class="chart-one">
      <canvas id="chart-one" width="500" height="400"></canvas>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="features-group success flipped">
  <div class="features feature-collapse white">
    <div class="text full">
      <h1 class="text-center">Get started in 10 minutes.</h1>
